    "description": "Zesty lemon-buttered basa is served over warm smashed beans and dill flecked potatoes. Here, we've used two types of beans: runner beans and butter beans. 'Smashed' simply means that instead of mashing until smooth, you'll lightly crush the potatoes which gives a more rustic texture and means less work for your arm. Smashing stuff!",
